WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.500 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:44.550 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:44.550 --> 00:00:46.090 align:middle line:10%
>>I first saw "A
Course in Miracles"

00:00:46.090 --> 00:00:48.630 align:middle line:10%
on someone's coffee
table in I suppose

00:00:48.630 --> 00:00:51.880 align:middle line:10%
1977, something like that.

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:54.450 align:middle line:90%
And I read the introduction.

00:00:54.450 --> 00:01:00.230 align:middle line:84%
And the introduction is a
kind of astonishing thing.

00:01:00.230 --> 00:01:01.010 align:middle line:90%
I have it here.

00:01:01.010 --> 00:01:04.450 align:middle line:90%


00:01:04.450 --> 00:01:09.080 align:middle line:84%
The introduction says, "This
is a course in miracles.

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:10.980 align:middle line:90%
It is a required course.

00:01:10.980 --> 00:01:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Only the time you
take it is voluntary.

00:01:13.960 --> 00:01:17.380 align:middle line:84%
Free will does not mean that you
can establish the curriculum.

00:01:17.380 --> 00:01:19.220 align:middle line:84%
It means only that
you can elect what

00:01:19.220 --> 00:01:21.380 align:middle line:84%
you want to take
at a given time.

00:01:21.380 --> 00:01:24.470 align:middle line:84%
The course does not aim at
teaching the meaning of love,

00:01:24.470 --> 00:01:26.890 align:middle line:84%
for that is beyond
what can be taught.

00:01:26.890 --> 00:01:29.640 align:middle line:84%
It does aim, however,
at removing the blocks

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:31.690 align:middle line:84%
to the awareness of
love's presence, which

00:01:31.690 --> 00:01:33.700 align:middle line:90%
is your natural inheritance.

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:36.720 align:middle line:84%
The opposite of love
is fear, but what

00:01:36.720 --> 00:01:39.630 align:middle line:84%
is all-encompassing
can have no opposite.

00:01:39.630 --> 00:01:41.550 align:middle line:84%
This course can therefore
be summed up very

00:01:41.550 --> 00:01:43.160 align:middle line:90%
simply in this way.

00:01:43.160 --> 00:01:45.320 align:middle line:90%
Nothing real can be threatened.

00:01:45.320 --> 00:01:47.730 align:middle line:90%
Nothing unreal exists.

00:01:47.730 --> 00:01:50.780 align:middle line:90%
Herein lies the peace of God."

00:01:50.780 --> 00:01:53.340 align:middle line:84%
I saw that, I read
it, and I thought

00:01:53.340 --> 00:01:57.010 align:middle line:84%
that was the most
amazing piece of writing.

00:01:57.010 --> 00:01:59.306 align:middle line:84%
To pick up a book and
have the book tell you

00:01:59.306 --> 00:02:01.335 align:middle line:90%
it's a required course.

00:02:01.335 --> 00:02:02.213 align:middle line:90%
You go, who was it?

00:02:02.213 --> 00:02:02.960 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Who is telling me that this
book is a required course?

00:02:05.770 --> 00:02:07.560 align:middle line:90%
I was so intrigued by that.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:09.160 align:middle line:90%
>>I read one page.

00:02:09.160 --> 00:02:11.740 align:middle line:84%
And that one page of reading,
and I heard for the first time,

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:14.750 align:middle line:84%
a little inner voice had
said, physician, heal thyself.

00:02:14.750 --> 00:02:16.319 align:middle line:10%
This is your way home.

00:02:16.319 --> 00:02:17.860 align:middle line:10%
And I had the most
amazing experience

00:02:17.860 --> 00:02:20.204 align:middle line:10%
of feeling a sense of
oneness with the whole world,

00:02:20.204 --> 00:02:21.870 align:middle line:10%
that there was
absolutely no separation,

00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:23.770 align:middle line:10%
that there was only love.

00:02:23.770 --> 00:02:26.270 align:middle line:10%
And a real feeling that I
was to be of service to God.

00:02:26.270 --> 00:02:27.853 align:middle line:84%
My whole life would
be changed, and it

00:02:27.853 --> 00:02:30.310 align:middle line:84%
would be a life of giving and
a life of being of service.

00:02:30.310 --> 00:02:31.726 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't understand
that, but it

00:02:31.726 --> 00:02:34.620 align:middle line:84%
was a very deep,
penetrating feeling.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And I became a student of the
course, fought it all the way.

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:39.950 align:middle line:84%
Couldn't deal with the thickness
of the course, let alone

00:02:39.950 --> 00:02:41.605 align:middle line:90%
its Christian terminology.

00:02:41.605 --> 00:02:43.355 align:middle line:84%
And yet there's something
about the course

00:02:43.355 --> 00:02:46.740 align:middle line:90%
that just compelled me to go on.

00:02:46.740 --> 00:02:49.630 align:middle line:84%
>>The spiritual genesis of
the international bestseller

00:02:49.630 --> 00:02:53.990 align:middle line:84%
"A Course in Miracles" is both
extraordinary and inspiring.

00:02:53.990 --> 00:02:57.520 align:middle line:84%
The self study three book course
was dictated by an inner voice,

00:02:57.520 --> 00:03:00.630 align:middle line:84%
and it has profoundly changed
the lives of countless people

00:03:00.630 --> 00:03:01.260 align:middle line:90%
the world over.

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:04.250 align:middle line:90%


00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:06.620 align:middle line:84%
Spread mainly by word
of mouth, its principles

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.250 align:middle line:84%
have thus far been known
only to its students.

00:03:09.250 --> 00:03:12.170 align:middle line:84%
But now its
transformational teachings

00:03:12.170 --> 00:03:15.190 align:middle line:84%
of love, forgiveness,
inner peace and wisdom

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.392 align:middle line:90%
will be explored.

00:03:17.392 --> 00:03:19.350 align:middle line:84%
Communicating the correct
meaning of the course

00:03:19.350 --> 00:03:22.055 align:middle line:84%
rests largely with Dr.
Kenneth Wapnick, president

00:03:22.055 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
of the Foundation for
"A Course in Miracles."

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:26.610 align:middle line:10%
In a recent
television interview,

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:30.310 align:middle line:10%
he gave an enlightening
overview of the course.

00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:33.760 align:middle line:10%
>>It's a form of
spiritual psychotherapy

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:36.260 align:middle line:10%
that comes to us in
a Christian context.

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:39.850 align:middle line:10%
As you mentioned at the
beginning, its author is Jesus.

00:03:39.850 --> 00:03:42.260 align:middle line:84%
But it's a Christianity
that has practically nothing

00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:45.350 align:middle line:84%
to do with the traditional
teachings of 2,000 years.

00:03:45.350 --> 00:03:48.290 align:middle line:84%
It certainly has nothing to do
with the Jesus of the Bible.

00:03:48.290 --> 00:03:50.860 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:53.110 align:middle line:84%
Its principal message
is forgiveness,

00:03:53.110 --> 00:03:55.720 align:middle line:84%
and that the way that we
remember our identity as God's

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:58.840 align:middle line:84%
children and realize that
in his eyes we are all one

00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:02.000 align:middle line:90%
is to forgive each other.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:04.300 align:middle line:84%
It basically is a self-study
course in the sense

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:06.809 align:middle line:84%
that you don't need
anyone outside.

00:04:06.809 --> 00:04:08.350 align:middle line:84%
The teacher, or the
guru, as it were,

00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:10.125 align:middle line:84%
would be Jesus or
the Holy Spirit,

00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:13.630 align:middle line:90%
who guides us day by day.

00:04:13.630 --> 00:04:16.522 align:middle line:84%
Our lives in this world are
seen as a classroom basically,

00:04:16.522 --> 00:04:17.980 align:middle line:84%
in which we learn
the Holy Spirit's

00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:19.959 align:middle line:90%
lessons of forgiveness.

00:04:19.959 --> 00:04:22.500 align:middle line:84%
And again, as I
mentioned, it's by undoing

00:04:22.500 --> 00:04:24.865 align:middle line:84%
all of the feelings
of inadequacy,

00:04:24.865 --> 00:04:26.860 align:middle line:84%
our feelings of
guilt, our anxieties,

00:04:26.860 --> 00:04:28.884 align:middle line:84%
which is what
forgiveness brings about,

00:04:28.884 --> 00:04:31.050 align:middle line:84%
that the love of God, which
is present in all of us,

00:04:31.050 --> 00:04:32.620 align:middle line:90%
is allowed to be remembered.

00:04:32.620 --> 00:04:37.110 align:middle line:10%
>>There is a massive effort
going on in this society,

00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:39.850 align:middle line:10%
and I think
throughout the world,

00:04:39.850 --> 00:04:43.120 align:middle line:10%
to retrieve some lost
part of ourselves.

00:04:43.120 --> 00:04:45.270 align:middle line:84%
And "A Course in Miracles"
is part of that effort.

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:53.220 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.220 --> 00:04:55.960 align:middle line:84%
>>"A Course in Miracles"
contains a whole philosophy

00:04:55.960 --> 00:04:57.710 align:middle line:90%
for living in our times.

00:04:57.710 --> 00:05:00.790 align:middle line:84%
The "Course" was born when an
inner voice spoke to Dr. Helen

00:05:00.790 --> 00:05:05.530 align:middle line:84%
Schucman in 1965 while she was
working at Columbia University.

00:05:05.530 --> 00:05:08.190 align:middle line:84%
Helen was a highly respected
research psychologist

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:10.930 align:middle line:84%
and associate professor
who worked with Dr. William

00:05:10.930 --> 00:05:13.540 align:middle line:84%
Thetford, a professor
of medical psychology

00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:15.460 align:middle line:84%
at the prestigious
Columbia University's

00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:18.560 align:middle line:84%
College of Physicians
and Surgeons.

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:20.350 align:middle line:10%
In her unpublished
autobiography,

00:05:20.350 --> 00:05:23.950 align:middle line:10%
Helen, who died on
February 9, 1981,

00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:27.150 align:middle line:10%
described her reactions to her
job and the highly stressful

00:05:27.150 --> 00:05:29.060 align:middle line:10%
situations that existed there.

00:05:29.060 --> 00:05:32.430 align:middle line:90%


00:05:32.430 --> 00:05:35.110 align:middle line:84%
>>I was a
psychologist, educated,

00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:38.550 align:middle line:84%
conservative in theory
and atheistic in belief.

00:05:38.550 --> 00:05:41.960 align:middle line:84%
I was working in a prestigious
and highly academic setting,

00:05:41.960 --> 00:05:45.360 align:middle line:84%
and the job was
ghastly at first.

00:05:45.360 --> 00:05:48.500 align:middle line:84%
The hospital didn't provide
space for our projects,

00:05:48.500 --> 00:05:51.960 align:middle line:84%
and when we were finally housed
in the new research building,

00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:54.530 align:middle line:84%
it was the most
difficult situation

00:05:54.530 --> 00:05:57.580 align:middle line:90%
of my professional life.

00:05:57.580 --> 00:05:59.890 align:middle line:84%
The work was oppressive
and carried out

00:05:59.890 --> 00:06:03.310 align:middle line:84%
in an atmosphere of suspicion
and competitiveness,

00:06:03.310 --> 00:06:08.070 align:middle line:84%
and interpersonal harmony
was depressingly lacking.

00:06:08.070 --> 00:06:10.310 align:middle line:84%
Then something
happened that triggered

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:13.230 align:middle line:84%
a chain of events I could
never have predicted.

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:17.890 align:middle line:10%
>>We had worked together
for a number of years

00:06:17.890 --> 00:06:25.290 align:middle line:10%
actually, from 1958
until the summer of 1965,

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:28.010 align:middle line:10%
with a good deal of
improvement in terms

00:06:28.010 --> 00:06:30.920 align:middle line:10%
of the organization
of the psychology

00:06:30.920 --> 00:06:32.510 align:middle line:10%
department at the hospital.

00:06:32.510 --> 00:06:34.840 align:middle line:90%
But we weren't really at peace.

00:06:34.840 --> 00:06:38.390 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I gave
Helen a little speech.

00:06:38.390 --> 00:06:43.360 align:middle line:84%
This was in June of 1965 before
we were going to a meeting.

00:06:43.360 --> 00:06:45.870 align:middle line:84%
Essentially, what
I said is, there

00:06:45.870 --> 00:06:50.230 align:middle line:84%
must be a better way of living
and working in the world,

00:06:50.230 --> 00:06:54.140 align:middle line:84%
of handling our personal and
professional relationships

00:06:54.140 --> 00:06:57.980 align:middle line:84%
and problems, and I'm
determined to find it.

00:06:57.980 --> 00:07:00.020 align:middle line:84%
This was kind of a
long speech for me,

00:07:00.020 --> 00:07:02.160 align:middle line:84%
and I remember feeling
at the end of this

00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:04.190 align:middle line:84%
that Helen probably
was going to laugh.

00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:07.350 align:middle line:84%
But to my amazement,
quite the contrary.

00:07:07.350 --> 00:07:09.900 align:middle line:84%
She said, you're
absolutely right, Bill.

00:07:09.900 --> 00:07:12.460 align:middle line:84%
We'll find this
other way together.

00:07:12.460 --> 00:07:16.140 align:middle line:84%
And that was the beginning
of a joint commitment,

00:07:16.140 --> 00:07:18.210 align:middle line:90%
which the two of us made.

00:07:18.210 --> 00:07:23.350 align:middle line:84%
The summer of 1965 was
an extraordinary summer

00:07:23.350 --> 00:07:27.100 align:middle line:84%
for both Helen and me
in a number of ways.

00:07:27.100 --> 00:07:29.920 align:middle line:84%
Helen began to have
a great deal of what

00:07:29.920 --> 00:07:35.690 align:middle line:84%
you might call heightened visual
imagery, or dream sequences.

00:07:35.690 --> 00:07:40.550 align:middle line:84%
She began to experience this
with considerable clarity.

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And I suggested that she
write down these experiences

00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:48.190 align:middle line:84%
as they occurred because
they seem to have something--

00:07:48.190 --> 00:07:50.390 align:middle line:84%
they were saying
something very important,

00:07:50.390 --> 00:07:54.430 align:middle line:84%
even though we didn't know
exactly what that was.

00:07:54.430 --> 00:07:58.126 align:middle line:84%
One of those sequences
involved being in a boat.

00:07:58.126 --> 00:08:09.620 align:middle line:90%


00:08:09.620 --> 00:08:12.580 align:middle line:84%
>>The boat was moving
slowly but easily

00:08:12.580 --> 00:08:14.460 align:middle line:84%
along a very straight
little canal.

00:08:14.460 --> 00:08:21.610 align:middle line:90%


00:08:21.610 --> 00:08:24.250 align:middle line:84%
There was just enough breeze
to help the boat along.

00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:28.100 align:middle line:90%


00:08:28.100 --> 00:08:30.650 align:middle line:84%
I wonder if there is
buried treasure here,

00:08:30.650 --> 00:08:33.110 align:middle line:90%
I thought to myself dreamily.

00:08:33.110 --> 00:08:35.422 align:middle line:84%
I shouldn't be
surprised if there were.

00:08:35.422 --> 00:08:49.500 align:middle line:90%


00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:52.460 align:middle line:84%
Then I noticed a long
pole with a large hook

00:08:52.460 --> 00:08:55.520 align:middle line:84%
on the end lying on
the bottom of the boat.

00:08:55.520 --> 00:08:57.680 align:middle line:84%
Just the thing, I
thought, dropping the hook

00:08:57.680 --> 00:09:02.180 align:middle line:84%
into the water and reaching the
pole down as far as I could.

00:09:02.180 --> 00:09:04.980 align:middle line:84%
The hook caught something
heavy, and I raised it

00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:07.930 align:middle line:90%
with difficulty.

00:09:07.930 --> 00:09:10.760 align:middle line:84%
It was an ancient
treasure chest,

00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:13.640 align:middle line:84%
the wood worn from the
water, and the bottom

00:09:13.640 --> 00:09:14.515 align:middle line:90%
covered with seaweed.

00:09:14.515 --> 00:09:17.710 align:middle line:90%


00:09:17.710 --> 00:09:21.080 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing in the
chest but a large black book,

00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:24.500 align:middle line:84%
like the spring binders used for
holding manuscripts or papers

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:27.010 align:middle line:90%
together.

00:09:27.010 --> 00:09:30.780 align:middle line:84%
On the spine, one word
was written in gold.

00:09:30.780 --> 00:09:34.500 align:middle line:90%
The word was Aesculapius.

00:09:34.500 --> 00:09:37.230 align:middle line:84%
The word was familiar,
but I could not

00:09:37.230 --> 00:09:39.390 align:middle line:90%
remember what it meant.

00:09:39.390 --> 00:09:41.620 align:middle line:84%
When I looked it
up, I found that it

00:09:41.620 --> 00:09:44.240 align:middle line:84%
was the name of the
Greek god of healing.

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:53.990 align:middle line:90%


00:09:53.990 --> 00:09:58.310 align:middle line:84%
I saw the same book once
more a few nights later.

00:09:58.310 --> 00:10:01.120 align:middle line:84%
This time, there was a
string of pearls around it.

00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:12.380 align:middle line:90%


00:10:12.380 --> 00:10:14.950 align:middle line:84%
This psychic phase
ended abruptly

00:10:14.950 --> 00:10:18.130 align:middle line:84%
with a particularly
clear picture episode

00:10:18.130 --> 00:10:23.950 align:middle line:84%
in which I knew I had made
an irrevocable choice.

00:10:23.950 --> 00:10:28.950 align:middle line:84%
I saw myself entering a cave
cut into a rock formation

00:10:28.950 --> 00:10:31.265 align:middle line:90%
on a bleak, windswept sea coast.

00:10:31.265 --> 00:10:52.970 align:middle line:90%


00:10:52.970 --> 00:10:57.140 align:middle line:84%
What I found in the cave
was a large and very old

00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:58.190 align:middle line:90%
parchment scroll.

00:10:58.190 --> 00:11:03.380 align:middle line:90%


00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:06.660 align:middle line:84%
Its ends were attached to
heavy gold-tipped poles,

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:08.960 align:middle line:84%
and the scroll was
wrapped around them

00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:11.690 align:middle line:84%
so that they met in the
middle of the scroll

00:11:11.690 --> 00:11:13.265 align:middle line:90%
and were tied tightly together.

00:11:13.265 --> 00:11:18.920 align:middle line:90%


00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:22.510 align:middle line:84%
I managed to untie the ends
and open the scroll just enough

00:11:22.510 --> 00:11:27.440 align:middle line:84%
to reveal the center panel, on
which two words were written,

00:11:27.440 --> 00:11:29.080 align:middle line:90%
God is.

00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:32.150 align:middle line:90%


00:11:32.150 --> 00:11:36.070 align:middle line:84%
Then I unrolled the scroll
all the way, and as I did so,

00:11:36.070 --> 00:11:41.480 align:middle line:84%
tiny letters began to appear
on both sides of the panel.

00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:44.460 align:middle line:84%
The silent voice which
I had heard before

00:11:44.460 --> 00:11:49.460 align:middle line:84%
explained the situation
mentally to me.

00:11:49.460 --> 00:11:50.950 align:middle line:84%
If you look at
the left side, you

00:11:50.950 --> 00:11:54.270 align:middle line:84%
will be able to read the
past, said the voice.

00:11:54.270 --> 00:11:55.720 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
right side, you

00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:58.560 align:middle line:90%
will be able to read the future.

00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:01.340 align:middle line:84%
But I hesitated only a
moment before rolling up

00:12:01.340 --> 00:12:04.340 align:middle line:84%
the scroll sufficiently
to conceal everything

00:12:04.340 --> 00:12:06.860 align:middle line:90%
except the center panel.

00:12:06.860 --> 00:12:10.120 align:middle line:84%
I am not interested in reading
the past or the future,

00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:11.890 align:middle line:90%
I said with finality.

00:12:11.890 --> 00:12:13.878 align:middle line:90%
I will just stop with this.

00:12:13.878 --> 00:12:18.990 align:middle line:90%


00:12:18.990 --> 00:12:24.410 align:middle line:84%
The voice sounded both
reassured and reassuring.

00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:26.940 align:middle line:90%
You made it that time, it said.

00:12:26.940 --> 00:12:27.645 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:12:27.645 --> 00:12:30.230 align:middle line:90%


00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:32.510 align:middle line:90%
And that, it seemed, was that.

00:12:32.510 --> 00:12:38.950 align:middle line:90%


00:12:38.950 --> 00:12:43.260 align:middle line:10%
>>Helen prided herself as a
research psychologist, not as

00:12:43.260 --> 00:12:47.210 align:middle line:10%
someone who heard voices,
who had heightened

00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:49.980 align:middle line:10%
visual imagery,
