conflict that they

00:19:47.947 --> 00:19:50.280 align:middle line:84%
had with each other and the
difficulties with the course

00:19:50.280 --> 00:19:52.430 align:middle line:84%
or resistances to the
course, that there's

00:19:52.430 --> 00:19:57.566 align:middle line:84%
underlying commitment that they
both had made, to see to it

00:19:57.566 --> 00:19:59.440 align:middle line:84%
that the purity of the
course and its message

00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.300 align:middle line:84%
would never be changed, and
would always remain pure.

00:20:02.300 --> 00:20:06.570 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that always
was extremely impressive to me.

00:20:06.570 --> 00:20:08.636 align:middle line:84%
Helen and I spent a great
deal of time together.

00:20:08.636 --> 00:20:11.010 align:middle line:84%
We had dinner almost every
night, she, her husband Louie,

00:20:11.010 --> 00:20:12.720 align:middle line:90%
and myself.

00:20:12.720 --> 00:20:15.330 align:middle line:84%
And we spent a great deal of
time going over the manuscript,

00:20:15.330 --> 00:20:17.590 align:middle line:84%
making sure that its
published form would

00:20:17.590 --> 00:20:20.360 align:middle line:84%
be exactly the way
Jesus wanted it.

00:20:20.360 --> 00:20:23.470 align:middle line:84%
And Helen herself was
an extraordinary woman.

00:20:23.470 --> 00:20:30.470 align:middle line:84%
She would go from moments of
real kind of other worldliness,

00:20:30.470 --> 00:20:33.060 align:middle line:84%
where her whole
face would change.

00:20:33.060 --> 00:20:35.770 align:middle line:84%
And she would tell me afterwards
