>>One of the things I've learned
from working with clients

00:45:49.860 --> 00:45:52.010 align:middle line:84%
in psychotherapy
is that they tend

00:45:52.010 --> 00:45:54.080 align:middle line:84%
to get better when they
take responsibility

00:45:54.080 --> 00:45:55.500 align:middle line:90%
for their experience.

00:45:55.500 --> 00:45:57.940 align:middle line:10%
And the "Course" speaks
to this very directly.

00:45:57.940 --> 00:46:01.960 align:middle line:10%
It says simply, I am
responsible for what I see.

00:46:01.960 --> 00:46:04.130 align:middle line:10%
I choose the feelings
that I experience,

00:46:04.130 --> 00:46:06.630 align:middle line:10%
and I decide upon the
goal I would achieve.

00:46:06.630 --> 00:46:08.980 align:middle line:84%
And everything that
seems to happen to me I

00:46:08.980 --> 00:46:12.570 align:middle line:84%
ask for and receive
as I have asked.

00:46:12.570 --> 00:46:15.070 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's quite a
challenge, if we're

00:46:15.070 --> 00:46:17.460 align:middle line:84%
going to accept
that at face value.

00:46:17.460 --> 00:46:20.430 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, it gives
us a sense of direction.

00:46:20.430 --> 00:46:23.910 align:middle line:84%
It points out to us that we
need to take responsibility

00:46:23.910 --> 00:46:28.260 align:middle line:84%
for the feelings we have
and that if I'm angry,

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:30.200 align:middle line:90%
at some level, that's a choice.

00:46:30.200 --> 00:46:32.150 align:middle line:90%
It may be out of defensiveness.

00:46:32.150 --> 00:46:34.070 align:middle line:90%
It may be out of fear.

00:46:34.070 --> 00:46:37.530 align:middle line:84%
But that basically, I
can choose whether I

00:46:37.530 --> 00:46:42.210 align:middle line:84%
want to release that anger, to
work it through and move on,

00:46:42.210 --> 00:46:46.220 align:middle line:84%
or whether I want to remain
stuck in it, so to speak.

00:46:46.220 --> 00:46:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
sometimes a problem.

00:46:48.230 --> 00:46:50.460 align:middle line:84%
Because in
psychotherapy, we often

00:46:50.460 --> 00:46:53.090 align:middle line:84%
emphasize the importance
of expressing anger,

00:46:53.090 --> 00:46:55.560 align:middle line:84%
but we forget that
that's not an endpoint.

00:46:55.560 --> 00:46:57.980 align:middle line:84%
When a person feels
like a victim,

00:46:57.980 --> 00:47:01.020 align:middle line:84%
it's maybe very appropriate
for them to get angry about it.

00:47:01.020 --> 00:47:03.790 align:middle line:84%
But it's also appropriate
for them to release that

00:47:03.790 --> 00:47:05.060 align:middle line:90%
and to move on.

00:47:05.060 --> 00:47:08.560 align:middle line:84%
So that in order to get in
touch with our creativity,

00:47:08.560 --> 00:47:11.880 align:middle line:84%
to be truly creative rather
than reactive in our lives,

00:47:11.880 --> 00:47:14.380 align:middle line:84%
we need to get beyond
the position of victim

00:47:14.380 --> 00:47:19.160 align:middle line:84%
and the position of adversary
and angry reactivity

00:47:19.160 --> 00:47:23.880 align:middle line:84%
into a more creative view of
what's possible in our lives.

00:47:23.880 --> 00:47:30.450 align:middle line:90%


00:47:30.450 --> 00:47:34.170 align:middle line:84%
>>You may believe that you are
responsible for what you do,

